### Coordinates and basic data
The community’s coordinates are 31°27′26″N 100°8′27″W (31.45722°N, 100.14083°W).  It is located in the [Country](/List_of_sovereign_states) United States, [State](/U.S._state) [Texas](/Texas), [County](/List_of_counties_in_Texas) [Tom Green County](/Tom_Green_County,_Texas).  

- **Elevation:** 1,755 ft (535 m) above sea level  
- **Time zone:** [Time_zone](/Time_zone) [UTC‑6](/UTC-6) (Central Standard Time) year‑round, with daylight saving time observed as [DST](/Daylight_saving_time) (UTC‑5) during summer  
- **ZIP code:** [ZIP_code](/ZIP_code) 76940  
- **GNIS feature ID:** 1362628  

### Historical and demographic notes
Mereta is also historically known as **Fisherville** or **Lipan**, names that appear in older geographic records.  The community is classified as an [unincorporated community](/Unincorporated_area) and maintains a [Post_office](/Post_office) under ZIP Code 76940.  

The [ZCTA](/ZIP_Code_Tabulation_Area) tabulation area for ZIP Code 76940 recorded a population of **138** individuals in the **[2000 census](/United_States_Census,_2000)**.  

The settlement was named by its first postmaster in honor of twin sisters, **Meta** and **Reta**, who lived in the area in 1902.  The townsite was officially [platted](/Plat) in 1904.  

